# An√°lise Completa ‚Äî Angular Frontend (`Sigah.SamWeb.Web`)

## 1. Angular Version & Key Dependencies

|------|---------|
| **Angular** | **5.2.11** (Angular CLI 1.7.4) |
| **TypeScript** | 2.6.1 |
| **RxJS** | 5.5.12 |
| **Node.js** | >=10.0.0 < 11 |
| **App Version** | 5.44.0 |

### Key Dependencies
| Package | Version | Purpose |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `ngx-bootstrap` | 2.0.5 | Modals, tooltips, typeahead, datepicker |
| `bootstrap` | 4.0.0-beta.2 | CSS framework |
| `admin-lte` | 2.4.2 | Admin UI theme |
| `angular2-hotkeys` | 2.1.5 | Keyboard shortcuts |

| `jquery` | 3.3.1 | DOM manipulation (legacy) |
| `ng-dynamic-component` | 2.3.0 | Dynamic components |

### Testing
- **Jest** 24.9.0 (NOT Karma/Jasmine)
- `jest-preset-angular` 8.4.0
- ESLint + TSLint for linting

---

## 2. TypeScript Configuration ([tsconfig.json](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/tsconfig.json))

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| `target` | es5 |
| `module` | esnext |
| `baseUrl` | `./src` |
| **Path alias** | `@/*` ‚Üí `./app/*` |
| `experimentalDecorators` | true |
| `emitDecoratorMetadata` | true |
| `downlevelIteration` | true |

---

## 3. Environment Configuration

### Runtime Config Files (`env*.json`)

Configuration is loaded at runtime via [app.config.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/app.config.ts) fetching `config/env.json`.

| Key | Docker (`env.docker.json`) | Dev (`env.dev.json`) | Prod (`env.prod.json`) |
|-----|----------------------------|----------------------|------------------------|
| `BACKEND_URL` | `http://localhost:8000/` | `http://app-desenv.hapvida.com.br/api/sam/sam-web/` | `http://samwebback.hapvida.com.br/` |
| `PEPSAM_BACKEND_URL` | `https://app-desenv.hapvida.com.br/api/pepsam` | `http://10.1.24.36:8080/api/pepsam` | `http://samwebback.hapvida.com.br:8080/api/pepsam` |
| `INTERNACAO_BACKEND_URL` | `https://app-desenv.hapvida.com.br/api/internacao/` | `http://app-desenv.hapvida.com.br/api/internacao/` | `http://app.hapvida.com.br/api/internacao/` |
| `TELEHEMATO_BACKEND_URL` | `http://localhost:8000/telehemato/` | Azure API Management | `https://api-lab.hapvida.com.br/assistance/telehemato/` |
| `PROTOCOLO_BACKEND_URL` | `https://app-desenv.hapvida.com.br/api/protocolo/...` | `http://app-desenv.hapvida.com.br/api/protocolo/...` | `http://app.hapvida.com.br/api/protocolo/...` |
| `AI_TRANSCRIPTION_URL` | `http://localhost:5000` | *(not set)* | *(not set)* |
| `AI_TRANSCRIPTION_TOKEN` | `dev-token` | *(not set)* | *(not set)* |
| `ENABLE_DATA_DOG` | `false` | `false` | `true` |

**Key observations:**
- **`AI_TRANSCRIPTION_URL`** and **`AI_TRANSCRIPTION_TOKEN`** are **only present in `env.docker.json`**
- When absent, [app.config.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/app.config.ts#L27) defaults to `https://anamneasy-265121215974.southamerica-east1.run.app` (Google Cloud Run)
- Interact (notification/documents) URLs present in dev/homolog/prod but not docker

### Angular Environments ([src/environments/](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/environments/))

Minimal ‚Äî only `production` flag and `baseApiUrl`. Mostly unused since runtime config via `env.json` takes precedence.

---

## 4. Module & Component Structure

### Root Module ([app.module.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/app.module.ts)) ‚Äî Monolithic

**NO lazy-loaded modules** ‚Äî everything is declared in `AppModule` (802 lines). Sub-modules:

| Module | Type |
|--------|------|
| `SharedModule` | Shared components/pipes |
| `ObservacaoLeitoModule` | Observation bed (lazy-candidate) |
| `InternacaoModule` | Hospitalization |
| `TransitionModule` | Page transitions |

## 5. Routing Structure ([app-routing.module.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/app-routing.module.ts))

**Preloading strategy**: `PreloadAllModules`

## 6. Authentication Mechanism

### Flow
1. **External SSO** ‚Üí `/:session/login/:datasource/:token` ‚Üí [LoginRedirectComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/login/login-redirect/login-redirect.component.ts)
   - Stores token + datasource in `sessionStorage` via `TokenService`
   - Fetches professional info, checks pending items
   - Redirects to `/:session/atendimento`

2. **Manual login** ‚Üí `/login` ‚Üí [LoginComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/login/login.component.ts)
   - Selects: datasource (HAP/SCHOSP) ‚Üí local ‚Üí m√©dico ‚Üí consult√≥rio ‚Üí especialidade
   - **Biometric verification** via popup
   - Calls `AutenticacaoService.logar()` ‚Üí `{pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/autenticacao/login`

### Token Storage
- [TokenService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/token.service.ts): All data in **`sessionStorage`**
  - `token`, `datasource`, `login`, `especialidade`

### HTTP Interceptor ([auth.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_interceptors/auth.service.ts))
Routes requests to different backends with different headers:

| URL Pattern | Headers |
|-------------|---------|
| `{pepsamBackendUrl}` (Java API) | `token: <token>` in header, URL params replaced |
| Django BFF (`BACKEND_URL`) | `Authorization: <token>`, `Data-Source: <datasource>` |
| Interna√ß√£o API | `Authorization: Bearer <token>` |
| Telehemato API | `Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key` |
| AI Transcription (`googleapis`) | `Content-Type: application/octet-stream` only |
| Protocolo API | No auth headers |

**URL templating**: Services use `{pepsamBackendUrl}` and `{dataSource}` placeholders in URLs, which the interceptor replaces at runtime.

### Guards (16 total)
Key guards: `AuthenticationGuard`, `AtendimentoGuard`, `CidsGuard`, `BlockedGuard`, `CanDeactivateIaTranscriptionGuard`

---

## 7. Services ‚Äî Complete Inventory (75+ services)

### Core API Services (via Django BFF ‚Äî `BACKEND_URL`)

| Service | Key Methods | API Endpoints |
|---------|-------------|---------------|
| [Cid10IaService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/cidIa.service.ts) | `getCidsIa()` | `POST {BACKEND_URL}dominios/diagnosticos/cids/{atendimento}/sugestao/` |
| [DominioService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/dominios.service.ts) | `tiposDocumento()` | `GET {BACKEND_URL}dominios/tipos-documentos/` |
| [AtendimentoInicialService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/atendimento-inicial.service.ts) | `atualizaEmergenciaClinica()`, `getComorbidades()`, `getAlergias()` | Various under `{BACKEND_URL}` |

### Core API Services (via Java PepSam ‚Äî `PEPSAM_BACKEND_URL`)

| Service | Key Methods | API Endpoints |
|---------|-------------|---------------|
| [AutenticacaoService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/autenticacao.service.ts) | `logar()`, `logout()`, `getLocais()`, `getMedicos()`, `getConsultorios()`, `getEspecialidades()`, `getTokenbiometria()`, `getHtmlbiometria()` | `{pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/autenticacao/*` |
| [TranscricaoAudioService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/anamnese/trascricao-audio/transcricao-audio.service.ts) | `sendDataAutioToAI()`, `isAudioTranscriptionActive()`, `getTranscriptionSignedUrl()`, `getTranscriptionResult()`, `justityRefuseTranscription()` | `{pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/postos/transcricao-audio/ativo`, `{pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/.../transcricao-voz/*` |
| [DiagnosticoInicialService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/diagnostico-inicial/services/diagnostico-inicial.service.ts) | `pesquisarDiagnosticoSugerido()`, `getSugestaoIaActive()`, `getJustificativaIaActive()`, `getDuplaBiometriaCidManualActive()`, `enviarJustificativaCid()` | `{pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/dominio/ia/*` |

### UI/Utility Services

## 8. CID Suggestion (AI) ‚Äî Detailed Flow

### Two Parallel AI Systems

#### A. `Cid10IaService` ‚Äî via Django BFF
- **File**: [cidIa.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/cidIa.service.ts)
- **Endpoint**: `POST {BACKEND_URL}dominios/diagnosticos/cids/{atendimento}/sugestao/?codigo_senha_master=X&ficha_nova=Y`
- **Flow**: Angular ‚Üí Django BFF ‚Üí Java API ‚Üí .NET AI API
- **Data**: Sends anamnesis fields, receives `Cid[]` results
- **Storage**: CID selections cached in `sessionStorage` per attendance

#### B. `DiagnosticoInicialService` ‚Äî via Java PepSam directly
- **File**: [diagnostico-inicial.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/diagnostico-inicial/services/diagnostico-inicial.service.ts)
- **Endpoint**: `POST {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/dominio/ia/sugestao-cid`
- **Check active**: `GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/dominio/ia/ativo`
- **Returns**: `DiagnosticoSugerido[]` ‚Äî grouped CID suggestions with confidence
- **Justification**: `POST {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/sugestao-protocolo/justificativa`

#### Feature Flags
- `sugestaoIaActive` checked at `DiagnosticoInicialComponent`
- `duplaBiometriaCidManualActive` ‚Äî requires dual biometric when selecting CID manually
- `justificativaIaActive` ‚Äî requires justification when rejecting AI suggestion

## 9. Voice/Speech Transcription (STT) ‚Äî Detailed Architecture

### Components & Services

| [AnamneseComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/anamnese/anamnese.component.ts) | Component | Hosts transcription, handles copy-to-HDA |

| [CanDeactivateIaTranscriptionGuard](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_utils/can-deactivate-ia-transcription.ts) | Guard | Prevents navigation during recording |

### Transcription Flow

```
1. AuthenticationGuard.checkRoute()
   ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.isAudioTranscriptionActive()
      ‚îî‚Üí GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/postos/transcricao-audio/ativo

2. AtendimentoInicialComponent renders AnamneseComponent
   ‚îî‚Üí AnamneseComponent renders TranscricaoAudioComponent (if active)

3. TranscricaoAudioComponent.recordingVerifications()
   ‚îî‚Üí Check parametrization (total/semTrava/justificativa/duplaBiometria)
   ‚îî‚Üí Show ModalTranscricaoAudioComponent (confirm recording)
   
4. startRecording()
   ‚îî‚Üí navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true })
   ‚îî‚Üí MediaRecorder with audio/webm or audio/ogg
   ‚îî‚Üí Health check every 2s, timeout 5s

5. stopRecording()
   ‚îî‚Üí sendoAudioToTranslate(audioBlob)
      ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.sendDataAutioToAI()
         ‚îú‚Üí getTranscriptionSignedUrl() ‚Üí GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/{cod}/evolucao/{num}/transcricao-voz/url-assinada
         ‚îî‚Üí PUT signed URL (GCS) with audio blob
      ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.getTranscriptionResult()
         ‚îî‚Üí Polls GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/.../transcricao-voz/resumo?workId=X
         ‚îî‚Üí Polls every 10s, up to 5 attempts, waits for non-202 response

6. openTranscriptionModal(transcription)
   ‚îî‚Üí ModalAudioTranscritoComponent
      ‚îú‚Üí "Copiar e aplicar no HDA" ‚Üí copies to queixa_principal (max 4000 chars)
      ‚îî‚Üí "Fechar" ‚Üí stores in transcricao_audio field only
```

### Recording Parameterization (via `CentralParametrizacaoService`)
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.total`**: Auto-start recording, no option to refuse
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.semTrava`**: Ask permission, if refused ‚Üí log justification
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.justificativa`**: Refusal requires written justification
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.duplaBiometria`**: Refusal requires biometric from 2 professionals

### State Machine (`IaTranscription` enum)
```
INITIAL ‚Üí RECORDING ‚Üí TRANSCRIPTION_LOADING ‚Üí TRANSCRIPTION_SUCCESS
                   ‚îî‚Üí RECORDING_ERROR        ‚îî‚Üí TRANSCRIPTION_ERROR
```

## 11. Docker Setup

### [Dockerfile](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/Dockerfile) (Production-like)
- Node 10.13.0, copies `env.docker.json` ‚Üí `src/config/env.json`, runs `ng serve`

### [Dockerfile.dev](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/Dockerfile.dev) (Development)
- Node 10.13.0, Angular CLI 1.7.4 global, hot-reload with `--poll 2000`
- Uses local `env.json` (not docker override)

### [docker-compose.yml](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/docker-compose.yml)
- 3 services: `app` (Angular:4200), `db` (Postgres:5432), `api` (Django:8000)
- Shared `sam-network` bridge

---

## 12. Code Conventions ([tslint.json](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/tslint.json))

- Directive prefix: `app` or `sam` (camelCase)
- Component prefix: `app` or `sam` (kebab-case)
- Variables: `allow-snake-case`, `allow-leading-underscore`
- Private members prefixed with `_`
- Component/directive class suffixes enforced

---

## 13. Key Observations

1. **Legacy codebase**: Angular 5 (2017), Node 10, TypeScript 2.6 ‚Äî significantly outdated
2. **Monolithic module**: All ~200+ components in single `AppModule` ‚Äî no lazy loading except `ObservacaoLeitoModule`
3. **Dual CID AI systems**: `Cid10IaService` (via Django) and `DiagnosticoInicialService.pesquisarDiagnosticoSugerido` (via Java) ‚Äî both active
4. **Voice transcription fully implemented**: Complete recording ‚Üí upload (GCS signed URL) ‚Üí polling ‚Üí display pipeline with biometric enforcement
5. **`{pepsamBackendUrl}` templating**: Unusual pattern where URL placeholders are resolved by the HTTP interceptor, not the services
6. **Session-based auth**: Token stored in `sessionStorage`, no JWT refresh mechanism visible
7. **DataDog RUM**: Integrated but disabled in dev/docker environments
8. **3,193 lines** in `AtendimentoInicialComponent` alone ‚Äî significant complexity in a single component

# Django BFF Analysis Report ‚Äî `Sigah.SamWeb.Api`

## 1. Overview

#### The `@service_method` Decorator Pattern

This is the **core pattern** of the entire project ‚Äî defined in [intmed_framework/services.py](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/intmed_framework/services.py#L57):

```python
@service_method(path='dominios/diagnosticos/cid10', source='lista_cid10')
def cids(self, search=""):
    params = { "faixa": "0-24" }
    if search:
        params['q'] = search
    return { 'params': params }
```

**How it works:**
1. Inspects the function's parameters and maps them to `kwargs`
2. Calls the decorated function to get custom request data (params, headers, body)
3. Formats the URL path using `{keyword}` substitution from `kwargs`
4. Makes an HTTP request via `self.http_request(method, path, data)`
5. If `source` is set, extracts that key from the JSON response
6. If `cached=True`, caches the response
7. The decorated function body can return `None` (pass-through) or a dict to override request data

### 7.2 `integracao/` ‚Äî Integration Layer

The bridge between Django and external APIs (primarily PEPSAM Java API).

#### Base Classes ([integracao/services/base.py](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/integracao/services/base.py))

- **`IntegracaoService`**: Extends `Service` with:
  - `base_url` = `settings.PEPSAM_API_URL`
  - **Token forwarding**: Extracts `HTTP_AUTHORIZATION` from Django request, strips "Bearer ", forwards as `token` header to PEPSAM
  - **Data-source**: Extracts `HTTP_DATA_SOURCE` header (either `HAP` or `SCHOSP`) ‚Äî determines which Oracle schema to query
  - **URL construction**: `{base_url}/{datasource}/{path}`
  - **Pagination**: Converts `page`/`page_size` to PEPSAM's `faixa` format

- **`InternacaoServiceAPI`**: Similar but uses `INTERNACAO_API_URL`

#### CID Suggestion Endpoint (AI/ML)

The critical `sugestao` method in `DiagnosticosService` at [line 93](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/dominio/services/dominio.py#L93):

```python
@service_method(
    method='post',
    path='dominios/diagnosticos/cid10/sugestao/{codigo_atendimento}/{codigo_senha_master}?fichaNova={ficha_nova}'
)
def sugestao(self, codigo_atendimento, codigo_senha_master, ficha_nova, **kwargs):
    pass
```

This **POSTs** to the Java API path `dominios/diagnosticos/cid10/sugestao/{atendimento}/{senhaMaster}`. The Java API then calls the .NET AI API for CID suggestions.

The view in [dominio/api/views.py](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/dominio/api/views.py#L101) (`CidsViewSet.sugestao_cid`):
1. Extracts archetype data from the request via `perform_arquetipo_route`
2. Calls `service.sugestao()` forwarding to Java
3. Serializes response through `CidSerializer`
4. Returns results

**URL**: `POST dominios/diagnosticos/cids/{codigo_atendimento}/sugestao/?codigo_senha_master=X&ficha_nova=Y`

**Authentication Flow**:

## 8. How Django Proxies to Java API (PEPSAM)

```
Angular Frontend
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº HTTP Request + Authorization token + data-source header
Django BFF (this project)
    ‚îÇ
    ‚îú‚îÄ Extracts token from Authorization header
    ‚îú‚îÄ Extracts data-source (HAP/SCHOSP) from custom header
    ‚îú‚îÄ Serializes input data (DRF serializers + Archetype system)
    ‚îú‚îÄ Transforms keys: snake_case ‚Üí camelCase (request)
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº HTTP Request via `requests` library
Java PEPSAM API ({PEPSAM_API_URL}/{data_source}/{path})
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº JSON response
Django BFF
    ‚îÇ
    ‚îú‚îÄ Transforms keys: camelCase ‚Üí snake_case (response)
    ‚îú‚îÄ Extracts specific fields via `source` parameter
    ‚îú‚îÄ Serializes output data
    ‚îú‚îÄ Handles errors (maps HTTP status codes to DRF exceptions)
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº JSON Response
Angular Frontend
```

The inflection transforms are defined in [intmed_framework/services.py](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/intmed_framework/services.py#L112):
- **Request**: `inflection.camelize` (snake_case ‚Üí camelCase)  
- **Response**: `inflection.underscore` (camelCase ‚Üí snake_case)

| [dominio/services/dominio.py#L93](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/dominio/services/dominio.py#L93) | `DiagnosticosService.sugestao()` ‚Äî POST to PEPSAM for CID-10 AI suggestion |
| [dominio/api/views.py#L101](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/dominio/api/views.py#L101) | `CidsViewSet.sugestao_cid()` ‚Äî View that handles the CID suggestion request with archetype data |
| [autenticacao/serializers.py#L35](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/autenticacao/serializers.py#L35) | `sugestao_cid_ia = BooleanField()` ‚Äî Flag in login response indicating if AI CID suggestions are enabled |

The Django BFF does **not** call the AI API directly. It sends the patient's archetype data (anamnesis, vital signs, etc.) to the Java API, which in turn calls the .NET AI service.

| Location | Reference |
|----------|-----------|
| [atendimentos/serializers/emergencia.py#L30](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/atendimentos/serializers/emergencia.py#L30) | `transcricao_audio` field ‚Äî Archetype field `FormRES_Emerg_Adulto_II.1.transcricao_audio` for storing audio transcription text in the emergency clinical form |

This is the **integration point** where VoiceTranscription results would feed into the clinical encounter data.

## 11. Deployment

### Deploy Script ([deploy_backend.sh](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/deploy_backend.sh))
- Interactive shell script for selecting environment (Dev/Homolog/Prod)
- Unzips `sam-web-api.zip` to `/sam/sam-web-api/`
- Copies appropriate `.env` file
- Runs `configure.sh` (installs deps + `cx_Oracle` + `collectstatic`)
- Restarts Apache (`apachectl restart`)

### Production: Runs behind Apache as WSGI

### Docker: Via `docker-compose.yml` at project root, `Dockerfile` uses `python:3.6.9` base

---

## 12. Summary of Key Architecture Patterns

1. **Service-ViewSet Pattern**: Every ViewSet has a `service_class` that handles the proxy call. Views are thin wrappers ‚Äî business logic lives in the Services.

2. **`@service_method` Decorator**: Declaratively maps Python methods to HTTP calls. The method body is optional ‚Äî if `pass`, all params are forwarded as-is. If it returns a dict, that dict overrides the request data.

3. **Archetype System**: OpenEHR-inspired form serialization. Each form field maps to an `id_componente` string. The `SugestaoSerializer`/`EvolucaoFormularioSerializer` convert between flat JSON and nested archetype structures.

4. **No Database**: All data comes from and goes to the PEPSAM Java API (which uses Oracle). Django's DB models are empty.

5. **Token Pass-through**: Authentication is fully delegated to PEPSAM ‚Äî Django just forwards the `Authorization` token.

## 6. Authentication Mechanism

### Flow
1. **External SSO** ‚Üí `/:session/login/:datasource/:token` ‚Üí [LoginRedirectComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/login/login-redirect/login-redirect.component.ts)
   - Stores token + datasource in `sessionStorage` via `TokenService`
   - Fetches professional info, checks pending items
   - Redirects to `/:session/atendimento`

2. **Manual login** ‚Üí `/login` ‚Üí [LoginComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/login/login.component.ts)
   - Selects: datasource (HAP/SCHOSP) ‚Üí local ‚Üí m√©dico ‚Üí consult√≥rio ‚Üí especialidade
   - **Biometric verification** via popup
   - Calls `AutenticacaoService.logar()` ‚Üí `{pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/autenticacao/login`

### Token Storage
- [TokenService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/token.service.ts): All data in **`sessionStorage`**
  - `token`, `datasource`, `login`, `especialidade`

### HTTP Interceptor ([auth.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_interceptors/auth.service.ts))
Routes requests to different backends with different headers:

| URL Pattern | Headers |
|-------------|---------|
| `{pepsamBackendUrl}` (Java API) | `token: <token>` in header, URL params replaced |
| Django BFF (`BACKEND_URL`) | `Authorization: <token>`, `Data-Source: <datasource>` |
| Interna√ß√£o API | `Authorization: Bearer <token>` |
| Telehemato API | `Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key` |
| AI Transcription (`googleapis`) | `Content-Type: application/octet-stream` only |
| Protocolo API | No auth headers |

**URL templating**: Services use `{pepsamBackendUrl}` and `{dataSource}` placeholders in URLs, which the interceptor replaces at runtime.

### Guards (16 total)
Key guards: `AuthenticationGuard`, `AtendimentoGuard`, `CidsGuard`, `BlockedGuard`, `CanDeactivateIaTranscriptionGuard`

## 8. CID Suggestion (AI) ‚Äî Detailed Flow

### Two Parallel AI Systems

#### A. `Cid10IaService` ‚Äî via Django BFF
- **File**: [cidIa.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/cidIa.service.ts)
- **Endpoint**: `POST {BACKEND_URL}dominios/diagnosticos/cids/{atendimento}/sugestao/?codigo_senha_master=X&ficha_nova=Y`
- **Flow**: Angular ‚Üí Django BFF ‚Üí Java API ‚Üí .NET AI API
- **Data**: Sends anamnesis fields, receives `Cid[]` results
- **Storage**: CID selections cached in `sessionStorage` per attendance

#### B. `DiagnosticoInicialService` ‚Äî via Java PepSam directly
- **File**: [diagnostico-inicial.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/diagnostico-inicial/services/diagnostico-inicial.service.ts)
- **Endpoint**: `POST {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/dominio/ia/sugestao-cid`
- **Check active**: `GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/dominio/ia/ativo`
- **Returns**: `DiagnosticoSugerido[]` ‚Äî grouped CID suggestions with confidence
- **Justification**: `POST {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/sugestao-protocolo/justificativa`

#### Feature Flags
- `sugestaoIaActive` checked at `DiagnosticoInicialComponent`
- `duplaBiometriaCidManualActive` ‚Äî requires dual biometric when selecting CID manually
- `justificativaIaActive` ‚Äî requires justification when rejecting AI suggestion

| [TranscricaoAudioFunctionService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/anamnese/trascricao-audio/transcricao-audio-function.service.ts) | Service | Navigation guard logic, modal orchestration |
| [AnamneseComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/anamnese/anamnese.component.ts) | Component | Hosts transcription, handles copy-to-HDA |
| [ModalAudioTranscritoComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/anamnese/trascricao-audio/modals/modal-audio-transcrito/modal-audio-transcrito.component.ts) | Modal | Shows AI transcription result, copy/apply |
| [ModalTranscricaoAudioComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/atendimento-inicial/anamnese/trascricao-audio/modals/modal-transcricao-audio/modal-transcricao-audio.component.ts) | Modal | Confirm start/stop recording |
| `InformativoRecusaTranscricaoComponent` | Modal | Refuse transcription warning |
| `ModalJustificativaLiberacaoTranscricaoComponent` | Modal | Justification for refusing |
| `ModalJustificativaLiberacaoTranscricaoDuplaBiometriaComponent` | Modal | Dual biometric for refusing |
| [CanDeactivateIaTranscriptionGuard](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_utils/can-deactivate-ia-transcription.ts) | Guard | Prevents navigation during recording |

### Transcription Flow

```
1. AuthenticationGuard.checkRoute()
   ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.isAudioTranscriptionActive()
      ‚îî‚Üí GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/postos/transcricao-audio/ativo

2. AtendimentoInicialComponent renders AnamneseComponent
   ‚îî‚Üí AnamneseComponent renders TranscricaoAudioComponent (if active)

3. TranscricaoAudioComponent.recordingVerifications()
   ‚îî‚Üí Check parametrization (total/semTrava/justificativa/duplaBiometria)
   ‚îî‚Üí Show ModalTranscricaoAudioComponent (confirm recording)
   
4. startRecording()
   ‚îî‚Üí navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true })
   ‚îî‚Üí MediaRecorder with audio/webm or audio/ogg
   ‚îî‚Üí Health check every 2s, timeout 5s

5. stopRecording()
   ‚îî‚Üí sendoAudioToTranslate(audioBlob)
      ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.sendDataAutioToAI()
         ‚îú‚Üí getTranscriptionSignedUrl() ‚Üí GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/{cod}/evolucao/{num}/transcricao-voz/url-assinada
         ‚îî‚Üí PUT signed URL (GCS) with audio blob
      ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.getTranscriptionResult()
         ‚îî‚Üí Polls GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/.../transcricao-voz/resumo?workId=X
         ‚îî‚Üí Polls every 10s, up to 5 attempts, waits for non-202 response

6. openTranscriptionModal(transcription)
   ‚îî‚Üí ModalAudioTranscritoComponent
      ‚îú‚Üí "Copiar e aplicar no HDA" ‚Üí copies to queixa_principal (max 4000 chars)
      ‚îî‚Üí "Fechar" ‚Üí stores in transcricao_audio field only
```

### Recording Parameterization (via `CentralParametrizacaoService`)
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.total`**: Auto-start recording, no option to refuse
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.semTrava`**: Ask permission, if refused ‚Üí log justification
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.justificativa`**: Refusal requires written justification
- **`TIPO_DE_TRAVA.duplaBiometria`**: Refusal requires biometric from 2 professionals

### State Machine (`IaTranscription` enum)
```
INITIAL ‚Üí RECORDING ‚Üí TRANSCRIPTION_LOADING ‚Üí TRANSCRIPTION_SUCCESS
                   ‚îî‚Üí RECORDING_ERROR        ‚îî‚Üí TRANSCRIPTION_ERROR
```

## 11. Docker Setup

### [Dockerfile](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/Dockerfile) (Production-like)
- Node 10.13.0, copies `env.docker.json` ‚Üí `src/config/env.json`, runs `ng serve`

### [Dockerfile.dev](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/Dockerfile.dev) (Development)
- Node 10.13.0, Angular CLI 1.7.4 global, hot-reload with `--poll 2000`
- Uses local `env.json` (not docker override)

### [docker-compose.yml](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/docker-compose.yml)
- 3 services: `app` (Angular:4200), `db` (Postgres:5432), `api` (Django:8000)
- Shared `sam-network` bridge

---

## 12. Code Conventions ([tslint.json](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/tslint.json))

- Directive prefix: `app` or `sam` (camelCase)
- Component prefix: `app` or `sam` (kebab-case)
- Variables: `allow-snake-case`, `allow-leading-underscore`
- Private members prefixed with `_`
- Component/directive class suffixes enforced

---

## 13. Key Observations

1. **Legacy codebase**: Angular 5 (2017), Node 10, TypeScript 2.6 ‚Äî significantly outdated
2. **Monolithic module**: All ~200+ components in single `AppModule` ‚Äî no lazy loading except `ObservacaoLeitoModule`
3. **Dual CID AI systems**: `Cid10IaService` (via Django) and `DiagnosticoInicialService.pesquisarDiagnosticoSugerido` (via Java) ‚Äî both active
4. **Voice transcription fully implemented**: Complete recording ‚Üí upload (GCS signed URL) ‚Üí polling ‚Üí display pipeline with biometric enforcement
5. **`{pepsamBackendUrl}` templating**: Unusual pattern where URL placeholders are resolved by the HTTP interceptor, not the services
6. **Session-based auth**: Token stored in `sessionStorage`, no JWT refresh mechanism visible
7. **DataDog RUM**: Integrated but disabled in dev/docker environments
8. **3,193 lines** in `AtendimentoInicialComponent` alone ‚Äî significant complexity in a single component

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="arquitetura">
  <context>Workspace STT √© um multi-repo com 6 servi√ßos interdependentes. O contexto inicial documentava apenas VoiceTranscription (API + Consumer). Os 3 repos adicionais (Pep.SamWeb.Api, Sigah.SamWeb.Api, Sigah.SamWeb.Web) formam o sistema original AutoCid/SamWeb ‚Äî o frontend e backend que consomem o STT.</context>
  <decision>O workspace cobre dois sistemas convergentes: AutoCid (sugest√£o CID-10 via IA) e STT (transcri√ß√£o de voz). Ambos s√£o features do SamWeb usado por m√©dicos. Angular chama Django BFF e Java PEPSAM diretamente (dual backend pattern). Java PEPSAM orquestra chamadas para .NET CidPrediction e VoiceTranscription.Api. VoiceTranscription.Consumer √© independente (event-driven via Pub/Sub).</decision>
  <outcome>Contexto expandido para cobrir todos os 6 repos, rela√ß√µes, fluxos de dados e infraestrutura Docker.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="arquitetura">
  <context>Angular SamWeb tem dois caminhos paralelos para sugest√£o CID-IA: Cid10IaService (via Django BFF ‚Üí Java ‚Üí .NET CidPrediction) e DiagnosticoInicialService (direto Java PEPSAM ‚Üí .NET CidPrediction). Ambos ativos simultaneamente.</context>
  <decision>Manter awareness de que existem dois fluxos CID-IA paralelos. Qualquer mudan√ßa na sugest√£o CID precisa considerar ambos os caminhos. O fluxo via Django BFF usa o archetype system para enviar dados de anamnese.</decision>
  <outcome>Evitar implementar mudan√ßas em apenas um dos caminhos, quebrando o outro.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="arquitetura">
  <context>Java PEPSAM obt√©m configura√ß√µes da VoiceTranscription.Api (URL base, OAuth2 credentials, subscription key) diretamente do Oracle Database via `dominioDAO.obterPropriedadesTranscricaoVoz(b)`, n√£o de arquivos de configura√ß√£o.</context>
  <decision>Para alterar a URL ou credenciais do STT consumidas pelo Java, a mudan√ßa deve ser feita no Oracle DB, n√£o em properties files. O Java autentica no STT via OAuth2 client_credentials flow.</decision>
  <outcome>Evita buscar configura√ß√£o STT em pepsam.properties ‚Äî ela est√° no banco.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="arquitetura">
  <context>docker-compose.yml raiz referencia Insights.CidPrediction.Api que n√£o est√° presente no workspace. Build do servi√ßo csharp-api falha sem esse repo clonado.</context>
  <decision>Para ambiente Docker completo, √© necess√°rio clonar o repo Insights.CidPrediction.Api no workspace. Alternativamente, pode-se comentar o servi√ßo csharp-api no compose se n√£o for necess√°rio testar sugest√£o CID.</decision>
  <outcome>docker-compose up sem o repo CidPrediction falha. Documentado nas instru√ß√µes de setup.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="arquitetura">
  <context>Todos os endpoints Java PEPSAM usam path parameter {ds} (HAP ou SCHOSP) para selecionar datasource Oracle. Angular envia isso via header Data-Source. Django BFF extrai do header e injeta no path URL ao proxiar.</context>
  <decision>Ao gerar c√≥digo que interage com PEPSAM, sempre incluir o par√¢metro {ds}. No Django, o datasource vem do header HTTP_DATA_SOURCE. No Angular, do sessionStorage via TokenService.</decision>
  <outcome>Evita erros de rota 404 por omiss√£o do datasource.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="padr√µes">
  <context>Django BFF usa o decorator @service_method como pattern principal. O body do m√©todo decorado retorna None (pass-through) ou dict para override de request data. O decorator constr√≥i a URL, faz HTTP request ao PEPSAM, e faz inflex√£o snake_case‚ÜîcamelCase automaticamente.</context>
  <decision>Ao criar novos endpoints no Django BFF, seguir o padr√£o @service_method. M√©todos que apenas fazem proxy direto podem ter body `pass`. Para customizar params/headers, retornar dict com overrides. Nunca fazer HTTP calls manuais ‚Äî usar o framework do IntegracaoService.</decision>
  <outcome>Mant√©m consist√™ncia no Django BFF e aproveita transforma√ß√µes autom√°ticas de inflex√£o.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="padr√µes">
  <context>Angular SamWeb usa URL templating com placeholders {pepsamBackendUrl} e {dataSource} nos services, que s√£o resolvidos pelo HTTP interceptor auth.service.ts em runtime. Diferente do padr√£o normal de construir URLs completas no service.</context>
  <decision>Ao criar novos services no Angular SamWeb, usar placeholders {pepsamBackendUrl} e {dataSource} nas URLs. O interceptor resolve automaticamente e adiciona os headers de autentica√ß√£o apropriados baseado no padr√£o de URL detectado.</decision>
  <outcome>Mant√©m consist√™ncia e aproveita o mecanismo de autentica√ß√£o autom√°tica do interceptor.</outcome>
</lesson>

<lesson date="2026-02-12" category="tooling">
  <context>O docker-compose requer Oracle Database externo (VPN corporativa) e n√£o possui fallback local. Sem Oracle, Java PEPSAM e Django BFF n√£o funcionam.</context>
  <decision>Para desenvolvimento local via Docker, a VPN corporativa Hapvida deve estar ativa. N√£o existe Oracle containerizado no compose. Os hosts Oracle s√£o 10.1.23.75:1521 (Django) e dboradsv-scan.hapvida.com.br:1521 (Java/WildFly).</decision>
  <outcome>Consci√™ncia de que o ambiente Docker local n√£o √© self-contained ‚Äî depende de infraestrutura de rede corporativa.</outcome>
</lesson>

#### The `@service_method` Decorator Pattern

This is the **core pattern** of the entire project ‚Äî defined in [intmed_framework/services.py](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/intmed_framework/services.py#L57):

```python
@service_method(path='dominios/diagnosticos/cid10', source='lista_cid10')
def cids(self, search=""):
    params = { "faixa": "0-24" }
    if search:
        params['q'] = search
    return { 'params': params }
```

**How it works:**
1. Inspects the function's parameters and maps them to `kwargs`
2. Calls the decorated function to get custom request data (params, headers, body)
3. Formats the URL path using `{keyword}` substitution from `kwargs`
4. Makes an HTTP request via `self.http_request(method, path, data)`
5. If `source` is set, extracts that key from the JSON response
6. If `cached=True`, caches the response
7. The decorated function body can return `None` (pass-through) or a dict to override request data

## 8. How Django Proxies to Java API (PEPSAM)

```
Angular Frontend
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº HTTP Request + Authorization token + data-source header
Django BFF (this project)
    ‚îÇ
    ‚îú‚îÄ Extracts token from Authorization header
    ‚îú‚îÄ Extracts data-source (HAP/SCHOSP) from custom header
    ‚îú‚îÄ Serializes input data (DRF serializers + Archetype system)
    ‚îú‚îÄ Transforms keys: snake_case ‚Üí camelCase (request)
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº HTTP Request via `requests` library
Java PEPSAM API ({PEPSAM_API_URL}/{data_source}/{path})
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº JSON response
Django BFF
    ‚îÇ
    ‚îú‚îÄ Transforms keys: camelCase ‚Üí snake_case (response)
    ‚îú‚îÄ Extracts specific fields via `source` parameter
    ‚îú‚îÄ Serializes output data
    ‚îú‚îÄ Handles errors (maps HTTP status codes to DRF exceptions)
    ‚îÇ
    ‚ñº JSON Response
Angular Frontend
```

The inflection transforms are defined in [intmed_framework/services.py](Sigah.SamWeb.Api/project/intmed_framework/services.py#L112):
- **Request**: `inflection.camelize` (snake_case ‚Üí camelCase)  
- **Response**: `inflection.underscore` (camelCase ‚Üí snake_case)

## 12. Summary of Key Architecture Patterns

1. **Service-ViewSet Pattern**: Every ViewSet has a `service_class` that handles the proxy call. Views are thin wrappers ‚Äî business logic lives in the Services.

2. **`@service_method` Decorator**: Declaratively maps Python methods to HTTP calls. The method body is optional ‚Äî if `pass`, all params are forwarded as-is. If it returns a dict, that dict overrides the request data.

3. **Archetype System**: OpenEHR-inspired form serialization. Each form field maps to an `id_componente` string. The `SugestaoSerializer`/`EvolucaoFormularioSerializer` convert between flat JSON and nested archetype structures.

4. **No Database**: All data comes from and goes to the PEPSAM Java API (which uses Oracle). Django's DB models are empty.

5. **Token Pass-through**: Authentication is fully delegated to PEPSAM ‚Äî Django just forwards the `Authorization` token.

## 6. Authentication Mechanism

### Flow
1. **External SSO** ‚Üí `/:session/login/:datasource/:token` ‚Üí [LoginRedirectComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/login/login-redirect/login-redirect.component.ts)
   - Stores token + datasource in `sessionStorage` via `TokenService`

2. **Manual login** ‚Üí `/login` ‚Üí [LoginComponent](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/login/login.component.ts)
   - Selects: datasource (HAP/SCHOSP) ‚Üí local ‚Üí m√©dico ‚Üí consult√≥rio ‚Üí especialidade

- [TokenService](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_services/token.service.ts): All data in **`sessionStorage`**
  - `token`, `datasource`, `login`, `especialidade`

### HTTP Interceptor ([auth.service.ts](Sigah.SamWeb.Web/src/app/_interceptors/auth.service.ts))
Routes requests to different backends with different headers:

| URL Pattern | Headers |
|-------------|---------|
| `{pepsamBackendUrl}` (Java API) | `token: <token>` in header, URL params replaced |
| Django BFF (`BACKEND_URL`) | `Authorization: <token>`, `Data-Source: <datasource>` |
| Interna√ß√£o API | `Authorization: Bearer <token>` |
| Telehemato API | `Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key` |
| AI Transcription (`googleapis`) | `Content-Type: application/octet-stream` only |
| Protocolo API | No auth headers |

**URL templating**: Services use `{pepsamBackendUrl}` and `{dataSource}` placeholders in URLs, which the interceptor replaces at runtime.

### Transcription Flow

```
1. AuthenticationGuard.checkRoute()
   ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.isAudioTranscriptionActive()
      ‚îî‚Üí GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/postos/transcricao-audio/ativo

2. AtendimentoInicialComponent renders AnamneseComponent
   ‚îî‚Üí AnamneseComponent renders TranscricaoAudioComponent (if active)

3. TranscricaoAudioComponent.recordingVerifications()
   ‚îî‚Üí Check parametrization (total/semTrava/justificativa/duplaBiometria)
   ‚îî‚Üí Show ModalTranscricaoAudioComponent (confirm recording)
   
4. startRecording()
   ‚îî‚Üí navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true })
   ‚îî‚Üí MediaRecorder with audio/webm or audio/ogg
   ‚îî‚Üí Health check every 2s, timeout 5s

5. stopRecording()
   ‚îî‚Üí sendoAudioToTranslate(audioBlob)
      ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.sendDataAutioToAI()
         ‚îú‚Üí getTranscriptionSignedUrl() ‚Üí GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/{cod}/evolucao/{num}/transcricao-voz/url-assinada
         ‚îî‚Üí PUT signed URL (GCS) with audio blob
      ‚îî‚Üí TranscricaoAudioService.getTranscriptionResult()
         ‚îî‚Üí Polls GET {pepsamBackendUrl}/{ds}/atendimentos/.../transcricao-voz/resumo?workId=X
         ‚îî‚Üí Polls every 10s, up to 5 attempts, waits for non-202 response

6. openTranscriptionModal(transcription)
   ‚îî‚Üí ModalAudioTranscritoComponent
      ‚îú‚Üí "Copiar e aplicar no HDA" ‚Üí copies to queixa_principal (max 4000 chars)
      ‚îî‚Üí "Fechar" ‚Üí stores in transcricao_audio field only
```

**NuGet Sources**: Hapvida private Azure Artifacts feed (`https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/hapvidalabs/_packaging/Hapvida.Core/nuget/v3/index.json`) + NuGet.org

## 3. REST Endpoints

### `POST /api/v1` ‚Äî Emergency CID Prediction (BERT or Gemini 2.5)

**Controller**: [PredictController.cs](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/src/Hapvida.Insights.CidPrediction.Api/Controllers/v1/PredictController.cs#L23) ‚Üí `InvokeEndpointAsync()`

**Request body** (`PredictCommand`):
```json
{
  "id_paciente": "string",
  "id_prontuario": "string",
  "id_atendimento": "string",
  "sexo": "string",
  "dt_nascimento": "string",
  "conteudo_anamnese": "string",
  "codigo_modelo_ia": 0  // 0=Default(BERT), 1=BERT, 2=Gemini_2_5_Flash_Lite
}
```

**Response** (`PredictResultDto`):
```json
{
  "id_paciente": "string",
  "id_prontuario": "string",
  "id_atendimento": "string",
  "data": "2025-01-01",
  "hora": "12:00:00",
  "cids_provaveis": [
    { "cid": "K35.9", "prob": 0.85, "desc": "Apendicite aguda" }
  ],
  "codigo_modelo_ia": 0
}
```

**Flow**: `PredictController` ‚Üí MediatR ‚Üí `PredictCommandHandler` ‚Üí `PredictAiEndpointsService.PredictAiAsync()` ‚Üí routes by `AiModelType`:
- `Default` / `Bert` ‚Üí `AiModelBertService` ‚Üí `IPredictAiEndpoint` (Databricks)
- `Gemini_2_5_Flash_Lite` ‚Üí `AiModelGemini25FlLtService` ‚Üí `IGemini25FlLtEndpoint` (Google API)

---

### `POST /api/v1/int` ‚Äî Hospitalization/Evolution CID Prediction (Gemini 2.0 Flash)

**Controller**: [PredictController.cs](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/src/Hapvida.Insights.CidPrediction.Api/Controllers/v1/PredictController.cs#L31) ‚Üí `CreateExampleAsync()`

**Request body** (`CreateExampleCommand`):
```json
{
  "texto_sinais": "patient signs text",
  "texto_evolucao": "patient evolution text"
}
```

**Response** (`EvolutionsResultDto`):
```json
{
  "cids_sugeridos": [
    { "cid": "K35.9", "descricao": "Apendicite aguda", "probabilidade": 0.85 }
  ],
  "tempo_total_segundos": 2.5,
  "tempo_modelo_segundos": 1.8,
  "status": "sucesso"
}
```

**Flow**: `PredictController` ‚Üí MediatR ‚Üí `CreateExampleCommandHandler`:
1. Concatenates `texto_sinais` + `texto_evolucao` into a single text
2. **Anonymization step (DISABLED)**: `IAutoCidAiEndpoint` (Azure ML SPACY model) ‚Äî hardcoded to `false`
3. **Gemini call (old path)**: `IGeminiAiPort` ‚Üí `GeminiService` ‚Üí Gemini 2.0 Flash API
4. **GiminiEvolutionService** call: builds prompt from `UseDefault` config field, calls Gemini 2.0 Flash, parses JSON response, validates CID-10 format with regex
5. Returns `EvolutionsResultDto` with timing metrics

---

- `GET /health` ‚Äî Liveness probe
- `GET /ready` ‚Äî Readiness probe

## 5. Key Differences: Emergency vs Hospitalization

| Aspect | `/api/v1` (Emergency) | `/api/v1/int` (Hospitalization) |
|--------|----------------------|-------------------------------|
| **Command** | `PredictCommand` | `CreateExampleCommand` |
| **Input format** | Patient demographics + anamnesis (`conteudo_anamnese`, `sexo`, `dt_nascimento`) | Clinical text only (`texto_sinais`, `texto_evolucao`) |
| **AI Model Selection** | Caller chooses via `codigo_modelo_ia` (BERT=1 or Gemini 2.5=2, default=BERT) | Always Gemini 2.0 Flash Lite |
| **Prompt source** | BERT: No prompt (ML model). Gemini 2.5: System instruction from `Constants.SysPromptGemini25FlLt` | Prompt stored in `appsettings.json` ‚Üí `Core:Services[2].UseDefault` field |
| **Anonymization** | None | Was SpaCy-based, **hardcoded to disabled** (`if (false)`) |
| **Response format** | `PredictResultDto` (with patient IDs, `cids_provaveis`) | `EvolutionsResultDto` (with timing metrics, `cids_sugeridos`) |
| **Status code** | 200 OK | 201 Created |
| **CID format** | `{ cid, prob, desc }` | `{ cid, descricao, probabilidade }` |
| **Java env var** | `URL_SERVICO_MAIDA_SUGES_CID_REST` | `URL_SERVICO_MAIDA_ENVIAR_CID_INTERNACAO` |

## 7. DI Configuration ([Bootstrapper.cs](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/src/Hapvida.Insights.CidPrediction.Api/Bootstrapper.cs))

```
Program.cs ‚Üí AddAppContext<Program>()     [from Hapvida.Core.Api.Http ‚Äî registers MediatR, AutoMapper, FluentValidation, controllers]
           ‚Üí AddDomainContext()            [from Hapvida.Core ‚Äî scans Domain assembly for handlers/validators]
           ‚Üí AddServicesContext()          [from Hapvida.Core.Infra.Services.Http ‚Äî registers Refit clients via [HttpService] attribute]
           ‚Üí AddAiEndpointContext()        [custom Bootstrapper ‚Äî see below]
           ‚Üí ConfigureSwagger()
           ‚Üí AddOpenTelemetryContext()     [from Hapvida.Core.Infra.OpenTelemetry]
```

**`AddAiEndpointContext` registers**:
- `IReadOnlyCollection<EndpointSettings>` ‚Äî all 4 service configs from `Core:Services` array
- `IAutoCidAiEndpoint` ‚Äî Refit client ‚Üí Azure ML SpaCy endpoint
- `IGeminiEndpoint` ‚Äî Refit client ‚Üí Google Gemini 2.0 API
- `IGeminiService` ‚Üí `GeminiService` (scoped)
- `IGeminiAiPort` ‚Üí `GeminiAiAdapter` (scoped)
- `IPredictAiEndpointsService` ‚Üí `PredictAiEndpointsService` (scoped)
- `IAiModelBertService` ‚Üí `AiModelBertService` (scoped)
- `IAiModelGemini25FlLtService` ‚Üí `AiModelGemini25FlLtService` (scoped)
- `IGiminiEvolutionService` ‚Üí factory-resolved `GiminiEvolutionService` (scoped)

Note: `IPredictAiEndpoint` and `IGemini25FlLtEndpoint` are registered by `AddServicesContext()` via the `[HttpService]` attribute scanning.

**Critical pattern**: The `UseDefault` field serves dual purpose:
- For BERT/AutoCid: `boolean` ‚Äî whether to use default model deployment
- For Gemini 2.0 (`IGeminiEndpoint`): **contains the full system prompt as a string** ‚Äî this is how the hospitalization prompt is configured

Each service entry has `Resilience` config with Timeout (300s), CircuitBreaker (disabled), and Retry (3 attempts, 200ms wait).

## 11. CI/CD Pipeline ([azure-pipelines.yml](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/azure-pipelines.yml))

---

## 12. Key Architecture Patterns & Decisions

| Pattern | Implementation |
|---------|---------------|
| **CQRS** | Commands + CommandHandlers via MediatR. No queries ‚Äî write-only API |
| **Strategy** | `PredictAiEndpointsService` routes to BERT or Gemini based on enum |
| **Hexagonal (Ports & Adapters)** | `IGeminiAiPort` ‚Üí `GeminiAiAdapter` ‚Üí `GeminiService` |
| **Refit HTTP clients** | `IPredictAiEndpoint`, `IGemini25FlLtEndpoint`, `IAutoCidAiEndpoint` auto-generated from interfaces |
| **Resilience** | Timeout (300s), Retry (3 attempts), CircuitBreaker (disabled) per endpoint |
| **AutoMapper profiles** | Separate profiles for emergency (`ModelProfile`, `PredictProfile`) and hospitalization (`ModelProfileInt`) |
| **FluentValidation** | `PredictCommandValidator` (empty ‚Äî no validation), `CreateExampleCommandValidator` (validates `CustomField` not empty) |
| **Layered architecture** | 3-layer: Presentation ‚Üí Domain ‚Üí Service (Infrastructure) |
| **OpenTelemetry** | Traces exported to OTel Collector at `localhost:4317` |

### Notable Code Observations

1. **Anonymization is hardcoded disabled** ‚Äî `if (false)` in `CreateExampleCommandHandler` bypasses the SpaCy anonymization step entirely
2. **Dual Gemini call in hospitalization** ‚Äî `CreateExampleCommandHandler` calls BOTH `IGeminiAiPort` (raw) AND `IGiminiEvolutionService` (structured), but only uses the result from `IGiminiEvolutionService`
3. **Prompt-in-config anti-pattern** ‚Äî The `UseDefault` field of `IGeminiEndpoint` service config stores the entire system prompt (~500 chars), repurposing what was designed as a boolean flag
4. **Gemini 2.5 vs 2.0** ‚Äî Emergency uses the newer Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite with a hardcoded system prompt in `Constants.cs`; Hospitalization uses the older Gemini 2.0 Flash Lite with a configurable prompt
5. **CID-10 validation** ‚Äî `GiminiEvolutionService` validates CID format with regex (`^[A-Z][0-9][0-9](\.[0-9]{1,2})?$`) and has a multi-level fallback for parsing Gemini's JSON responses (clean JSON ‚Üí fragmented extraction ‚Üí line-by-line fallback)
6. **Redis dependency declared but unused** ‚Äî `StackExchangeRedis 8.0.6` is in Domain's dependencies but no caching code was found
7. **Typo in naming** ‚Äî "Gimini" vs "Gemini" inconsistency throughout (`GiminiEvolutionService`, `IGiminiEvolutionService`)

edits.text: Starts the AutoCid Docker environment using WSL (without Docker Desktop).
1. Checks prerequisites (WSL, Docker Engine in WSL)
2. Creates symlinks to map folder names expected by docker-compose
3. Starts Docker Engine in WSL if not running
4. Runs docker-compose up from within WSL
Stops all services instead of starting.
Forces rebuild of all images before starting.
Follows logs after starting (Ctrl+C to stop following).
# Folder name mappings: docker-compose expects -> actual folder name
Write-Err "WSL nao esta instalado ou habilitado."
Write-Err "Docker Engine nao encontrado no WSL."
Para instalar Docker Engine no WSL (Ubuntu/Debian):
sudo apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg

echo "deb [arch=`$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu `$(. /etc/os-release && echo `$VERSION_CODENAME) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
sudo apt-get install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-compose-plugin
Write-Host "  Instale: sudo apt-get install docker-compose-plugin" -ForegroundColor Gray
# 2. Create Symlinks (inside WSL for Linux FS)
# Check if symlink already exists and is correct

Write-Info "Pasta real '$linkName' ja existe ‚Äî assumindo que e o repo correto."
Write-Step "Verificando se Docker daemon esta rodando..."
# Wait for it to be ready

Write-Host "  Verifique manualmente: wsl sudo dockerd" -ForegroundColor Gray
Write-Host "  Ou tente: wsl sudo service docker start" -ForegroundColor Gray
# Wait a moment for containers to start

{"filePath": "d:\Repos\_hv\STT\docker-start-wsl.ps1", "content": "#!/usr/bin/env pwsh
<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Starts the AutoCid Docker environment using WSL (without Docker Desktop).

.DESCRIPTION
    This script:
    1. Checks prerequisites (WSL, Docker Engine in WSL)
    2. Creates symlinks to map folder names expected by docker-compose
    3. Starts Docker Engine in WSL if not running
    4. Runs docker-compose up from within WSL
    5. Shows service URLs and status

.PARAMETER Down
    Stops all services instead of starting.

.PARAMETER Build
    Forces rebuild of all images before starting.

.PARAMETER Logs
    Follows logs after starting (Ctrl+C to stop following).

.PARAMETER Service
    Start only a specific service (e.g., "csharp-api", "java-api", "python-api", "angular-web").

.PARAMETER Status
    Shows current status of containers.

.EXAMPLE
    .\docker-start-wsl.ps1                          # Start all services
    .\docker-start-wsl.ps1 -Build                   # Rebuild and start
    .\docker-start-wsl.ps1 -Logs                    # Start and follow logs
    .\docker-start-wsl.ps1 -Down                    # Stop all services
    .\docker-start-wsl.ps1 -Service java-api -Build # Rebuild only java-api
    .\docker-start-wsl.ps1 -Status                  # Check container status
#>

[CmdletBinding()]
param(
    [switch]$Down,
    [switch]$Build,
    [switch]$Logs,
    [string]$Service,
    [switch]$Status
)

$ErrorActionPreference = "Stop"

# =====================================================
# Configuration
# =====================================================
$WORKSPACE_WIN = $PSScriptRoot
$COMPOSE_FILE = "docker-compose.yml"

# Folder name mappings: docker-compose expects -> actual folder name
$SYMLINKS = @{
    "Assistance.Pep.SamWeb.Api"   = "Pep.SamWeb.Api"
    "Assistance.Sigah.SamWeb.Api" = "Sigah.SamWeb.Api"
    "Assistance.Sigah.SamWeb.Web" = "Sigah.SamWeb.Web"
}

# Service URLs for display
$SERVICE_URLS = @{
    "angular-web" = "http://localhost:4200"
    "python-api"  = "http://localhost:8000"
    "java-api"    = "http://localhost:8080/api/pepsam"
    "csharp-api"  = "http://localhost:5000/api/v1"
    "wildfly-admin" = "http://localhost:9990 (admin/admin)"
    "java-debug"  = "localhost:8787"
}

# =====================================================
# Helper Functions
# =====================================================
function Write-Header {
    param([string]$Text)
    Write-Host ""
    Write-Host "======================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "  $Text" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "======================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host ""
}

function Write-Step {
    param([string]$Text)
    Write-Host "[*] $Text" -ForegroundColor Yellow
}

function Write-Ok {
    param([string]$Text)
    Write-Host "[OK] $Text" -ForegroundColor Green
}

function Write-Err {
    param([string]$Text)
    Write-Host "[ERRO] $Text" -ForegroundColor Red
}

function Write-Info {
    param([string]$Text)
    Write-Host "[i] $Text" -ForegroundColor Gray
}

function Convert-ToWslPath {
    param([string]$WinPath)
    # D:\Repos\_hv\STT -> /mnt/d/Repos/_hv/STT
    $drive = $WinPath.Substring(0, 1).ToLower()
    $rest = $WinPath.Substring(2) -replace '\\', '/'
    return "/mnt/$drive$rest"
}

function Invoke-Wsl {
    param(
        [string]$Command,
        [switch]$PassThru,
        [switch]$NoCheck
    )
    if ($PassThru) {
        $result = wsl bash -c $Command 2>&1
        if (-not $NoCheck -and $LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) {
            Write-Err "Comando WSL falhou: $Command"
            Write-Host $result -ForegroundColor Red
            return $null
        }
        return $result
    }
    else {
        wsl bash -c $Command
        if (-not $NoCheck -and $LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) {
            Write-Err "Comando WSL falhou: $Command"
            return $false
        }
        return $true
    }
}

# =====================================================
# 1. Check Prerequisites
# =====================================================
function Test-Prerequisites {
    Write-Header "Verificando pre-requisitos"

    # Check WSL
    Write-Step "Verificando WSL..."
    $wslStatus = wsl --status 2>&1
    if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) {
        Write-Err "WSL nao esta instalado ou habilitado."
        Write-Host "  Instale com: wsl --install" -ForegroundColor Gray
        exit 1
    }
    Write-Ok "WSL disponivel"

    # Check Docker in WSL
    Write-Step "Verificando Docker Engine no WSL..."
    $dockerVersion = Invoke-Wsl -Command "docker --version 2>/dev/null" -PassThru -NoCheck
    if (-not $dockerVersion -or $LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) {
        Write-Err "Docker Engine nao encontrado no WSL."
        Write-Host @"
  Para instalar Docker Engine no WSL (Ubuntu/Debian):

    # Dentro do WSL:
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg
    sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
    curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
    sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
    echo "deb [arch=`$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu `$(. /etc/os-release && echo `$VERSION_CODENAME) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-compose-plugin
    sudo usermod -aG docker `$USER
"@ -ForegroundColor Gray
        exit 1
    }
    Write-Ok "Docker Engine: $($dockerVersion.Trim())"

    # Check docker compose
    Write-Step "Verificando docker compose..."
    $composeVersion = Invoke-Wsl -Command "docker compose version 2>/dev/null" -PassThru -NoCheck
    if (-not $composeVersion -or $LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) {
        Write-Err "docker compose plugin nao encontrado."
        Write-Host "  Instale: sudo apt-get install docker-compose-plugin" -ForegroundColor Gray
        exit 1
    }
    Write-Ok "Docker Compose: $($composeVersion.Trim())"

    # Check docker-compose.yml exists
    if (-not (Test-Path "$WORKSPACE_WIN\$COMPOSE_FILE")) {
        Write-Err "docker-compose.yml nao encontrado em $WORKSPACE_WIN"
        exit 1
    }
    Write-Ok "docker-compose.yml encontrado"
}

# =====================================================
# 2. Create Symlinks (inside WSL for Linux FS)
# =====================================================
function Set-Symlinks {
    Write-Header "Configurando symlinks"

    $wslPath = Convert-ToWslPath $WORKSPACE_WIN

    foreach ($link in $SYMLINKS.GetEnumerator()) {
        $linkName = $link.Key
        $targetName = $link.Value

        Write-Step "Verificando: $linkName -> $targetName"

        # Check if symlink already exists and is correct
        $exists = Invoke-Wsl -Command "test -L '$wslPath/$linkName' && readlink '$wslPath/$linkName' 2>/dev/null || echo 'NOT_FOUND'" -PassThru -NoCheck

        if ($exists -and $exists.Trim() -eq $targetName) {
            Write-Ok "Symlink ja existe: $linkName -> $targetName"
            continue
        }

        # Check if target folder exists
        $targetExists = Invoke-Wsl -Command "test -d '$wslPath/$targetName' && echo 'YES' || echo 'NO'" -PassThru -NoCheck
        if ($targetExists.Trim() -ne "YES") {
            Write-Err "Pasta alvo nao encontrada: $targetName"
            continue
        }

        # Check if a real directory with the link name exists (would block symlink)
        $realDirExists = Invoke-Wsl -Command "test -d '$wslPath/$linkName' && ! test -L '$wslPath/$linkName' && echo 'YES' || echo 'NO'" -PassThru -NoCheck
        if ($realDirExists.Trim() -eq "YES") {
            Write-Info "Pasta real '$linkName' ja existe ‚Äî assumindo que e o repo correto."
            continue
        }

        # Remove existing broken symlink
        Invoke-Wsl -Command "rm -f '$wslPath/$linkName'" -NoCheck | Out-Null

        # Create symlink
        $result = Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && ln -s '$targetName' '$linkName'" -NoCheck
        if ($LASTEXITCODE -eq 0) {
            Write-Ok "Symlink criado: $linkName -> $targetName"
        }
        else {
            Write-Err "Falha ao criar symlink: $linkName"
        }
    }
}

# =====================================================
# 3. Start Docker Engine
# =====================================================
function Start-DockerEngine {
    Write-Header "Verificando Docker Engine"

    Write-Step "Verificando se Docker daemon esta rodando..."
    $dockerRunning = Invoke-Wsl -Command "docker info >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo 'YES' || echo 'NO'" -PassThru -NoCheck

    if ($dockerRunning.Trim() -ne "YES") {
        Write-Step "Iniciando Docker daemon no WSL..."
        # Start dockerd in background
        Invoke-Wsl -Command "sudo nohup dockerd > /tmp/dockerd.log 2>&1 &" -NoCheck | Out-Null

        # Wait for it to be ready
        $maxRetries = 15
        $retry = 0
        do {
            Start-Sleep -Seconds 2
            $retry++
            $dockerRunning = Invoke-Wsl -Command "docker info >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo 'YES' || echo 'NO'" -PassThru -NoCheck
            Write-Host "  Aguardando daemon ($retry/$maxRetries)..." -ForegroundColor Gray
        } while ($dockerRunning.Trim() -ne "YES" -and $retry -lt $maxRetries)

        if ($dockerRunning.Trim() -ne "YES") {
            Write-Err "Docker daemon nao iniciou apos $maxRetries tentativas."
            Write-Host "  Verifique manualmente: wsl sudo dockerd" -ForegroundColor Gray
            Write-Host "  Ou tente: wsl sudo service docker start" -ForegroundColor Gray
            exit 1
        }
        Write-Ok "Docker daemon iniciado"
    }
    else {
        Write-Ok "Docker daemon ja esta rodando"
    }
}

# =====================================================
# 4. Docker Compose Operations
# =====================================================
function Invoke-DockerCompose {
    $wslPath = Convert-ToWslPath $WORKSPACE_WIN

    if ($Status) {
        Write-Header "Status dos Containers"
        Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose ps" -NoCheck
        return
    }

    if ($Down) {
        Write-Header "Parando servicos"
        Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose down" -NoCheck
        Write-Ok "Todos os servicos foram parados"
        return
    }

    # Build images
    if ($Build) {
        Write-Header "Construindo imagens"
        if ($Service) {
            Write-Step "Construindo imagem: $Service"
            Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose build --no-cache $Service"
        }
        else {
            Write-Step "Construindo todas as imagens..."
            Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose build --no-cache"
        }
        Write-Ok "Build concluido"
    }

    # Start services
    Write-Header "Iniciando servicos"

    if ($Service) {
        Write-Step "Iniciando servico: $Service"
        Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose up -d $Service"
    }
    else {
        Write-Step "Iniciando todos os servicos..."
        Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose up -d"
    }

    # Wait a moment for containers to start
    Start-Sleep -Seconds 3

    # Show status
    Write-Header "Status dos Containers"
    Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose ps" -NoCheck

    # Show URLs
    Write-Header "URLs dos Servicos"
    foreach ($svc in $SERVICE_URLS.GetEnumerator()) {
        Write-Host "  $($svc.Key.PadRight(16)) $($svc.Value)" -ForegroundColor White
    }

    # Show warnings
    Write-Host ""
    Write-Host "IMPORTANTE:" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "  - Oracle DB externo requer VPN corporativa Hapvida" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "  - Java API (WildFly) leva ~30-60s para inicializar" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "  - Primeiro build pode levar 10-15 min (download de dependencias)" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host ""

    # Follow logs if requested
    if ($Logs) {
        Write-Header "Seguindo logs (Ctrl+C para parar)"
        if ($Service) {
            Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose logs -f $Service" -NoCheck
        }
        else {
            Invoke-Wsl -Command "cd '$wslPath' && docker compose logs -f" -NoCheck
        }
    }
}

# =====================================================
# Main
# =====================================================
Write-Host ""
Write-Host "  AutoCid + STT - Docker Environment (WSL)" -ForegroundColor Magenta
Write-Host "  Workspace: $WORKSPACE_WIN" -ForegroundColor Gray
Write-Host ""

Test-Prerequisites
Set-Symlinks
Start-DockerEngine
Invoke-DockerCompose

Write-Host ""

"}

## 3. REST Endpoints

### `POST /api/v1` ‚Äî Emergency CID Prediction (BERT or Gemini 2.5)

**Controller**: [PredictController.cs](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/src/Hapvida.Insights.CidPrediction.Api/Controllers/v1/PredictController.cs#L23) ‚Üí `InvokeEndpointAsync()`

**Response** (`PredictResultDto`):


**Flow**: `PredictController` ‚Üí MediatR ‚Üí `PredictCommandHandler` ‚Üí `PredictAiEndpointsService.PredictAiAsync()` ‚Üí routes by `AiModelType`:
- `Default` / `Bert` ‚Üí `AiModelBertService` ‚Üí `IPredictAiEndpoint` (Databricks)
- `Gemini_2_5_Flash_Lite` ‚Üí `AiModelGemini25FlLtService` ‚Üí `IGemini25FlLtEndpoint` (Google API)

### `POST /api/v1/int` ‚Äî Hospitalization/Evolution CID Prediction (Gemini 2.0 Flash)

**Controller**: [PredictController.cs](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/src/Hapvida.Insights.CidPrediction.Api/Controllers/v1/PredictController.cs#L31) ‚Üí `CreateExampleAsync()`

**Request body** (`CreateExampleCommand`):
```json
{
  "texto_sinais": "patient signs text",
  "texto_evolucao": "patient evolution text"
}
```

**Response** (`EvolutionsResultDto`):
```json
{
  "cids_sugeridos": [
    { "cid": "K35.9", "descricao": "Apendicite aguda", "probabilidade": 0.85 }
  ],
  "tempo_total_segundos": 2.5,
  "tempo_modelo_segundos": 1.8,
  "status": "sucesso"
}
```

**Flow**: `PredictController` ‚Üí MediatR ‚Üí `CreateExampleCommandHandler`:
1. Concatenates `texto_sinais` + `texto_evolucao` into a single text
2. **Anonymization step (DISABLED)**: `IAutoCidAiEndpoint` (Azure ML SPACY model) ‚Äî hardcoded to `false`
3. **Gemini call (old path)**: `IGeminiAiPort` ‚Üí `GeminiService` ‚Üí Gemini 2.0 Flash API
4. **GiminiEvolutionService** call: builds prompt from `UseDefault` config field, calls Gemini 2.0 Flash, parses JSON response, validates CID-10 format with regex
5. Returns `EvolutionsResultDto` with timing metrics

## 11. CI/CD Pipeline ([azure-pipelines.yml](Insights.CidPrediction.Api/azure-pipelines.yml))

- **Triggers**: `develop`, `hotfix/*`, `release/*` branches ‚Äî only `src/*` path changes

## 12. Key Architecture Patterns & Decisions

| Pattern | Implementation |
|---------|---------------|
| **CQRS** | Commands + CommandHandlers via MediatR. No queries ‚Äî write-only API |
| **Strategy** | `PredictAiEndpointsService` routes to BERT or Gemini based on enum |
| **Hexagonal (Ports & Adapters)** | `IGeminiAiPort` ‚Üí `GeminiAiAdapter` ‚Üí `GeminiService` |
| **Refit HTTP clients** | `IPredictAiEndpoint`, `IGemini25FlLtEndpoint`, `IAutoCidAiEndpoint` auto-generated from interfaces |
| **Resilience** | Timeout (300s), Retry (3 attempts), CircuitBreaker (disabled) per endpoint |
| **AutoMapper profiles** | Separate profiles for emergency (`ModelProfile`, `PredictProfile`) and hospitalization (`ModelProfileInt`) |
| **FluentValidation** | `PredictCommandValidator` (empty ‚Äî no validation), `CreateExampleCommandValidator` (validates `CustomField` not empty) |
| **Layered architecture** | 3-layer: Presentation ‚Üí Domain ‚Üí Service (Infrastructure) |
| **OpenTelemetry** | Traces exported to OTel Collector at `localhost:4317` |

### Notable Code Observations

1. **Anonymization is hardcoded disabled** ‚Äî `if (false)` in `CreateExampleCommandHandler` bypasses the SpaCy anonymization step entirely
2. **Dual Gemini call in hospitalization** ‚Äî `CreateExampleCommandHandler` calls BOTH `IGeminiAiPort` (raw) AND `IGiminiEvolutionService` (structured), but only uses the result from `IGiminiEvolutionService`
3. **Prompt-in-config anti-pattern** ‚Äî The `UseDefault` field of `IGeminiEndpoint` service config stores the entire system prompt (~500 chars), repurposing what was designed as a boolean flag
4. **Gemini 2.5 vs 2.0** ‚Äî Emergency uses the newer Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite with a hardcoded system prompt in `Constants.cs`; Hospitalization uses the older Gemini 2.0 Flash Lite with a configurable prompt
5. **CID-10 validation** ‚Äî `GiminiEvolutionService` validates CID format with regex (`^[A-Z][0-9][0-9](\.[0-9]{1,2})?$`) and has a multi-level fallback for parsing Gemini's JSON responses (clean JSON ‚Üí fragmented extraction ‚Üí line-by-line fallback)
6. **Redis dependency declared but unused** ‚Äî `StackExchangeRedis 8.0.6` is in Domain's dependencies but no caching code was found
7. **Typo in naming** ‚Äî "Gimini" vs "Gemini" inconsistency throughout (`GiminiEvolutionService`, `IGiminiEvolutionService`)
